# Project Context
This is a static HTML/CSS/JS website with a custom responsive CSS framework.

## Key Files
- `assets/css/framework-unified.css` - Main framework with design tokens
- `assets/css/typography-system.css` - Typography system
- `assets/js/main.js` - Core site functionality
- Design tokens use CSS custom properties (--baseline, --gutter-*, etc.)

## Coding Standards
- Mobile-first responsive design
- Use CSS custom properties for all design tokens
- Follow baseline rhythm system (8px units)
- Maintain accessibility (ARIA labels, semantic HTML)
- Support light/dark themes
- Use semantic HTML5 elements
- Vanilla JavaScript (no frameworks)

## File Structure
- HTML pages in root
- CSS in `assets/css/`
- JS in `assets/js/`
- Images in `assets/images/`
- Icons in `assets/icons/`
- Documentation in `docs/`

## Important Patterns
- Grid system: `.container` > `.grid` > `.col-*`
- Theme toggle: `.theme-toggle` with `data-theme` attribute
- Navigation: `.nav` with mobile menu overlay
- Cards: `.card` with variants like `.card--glass-outline`

## Color Guidelines
- Always check colors work on both light and dark themes
- Use CSS custom properties for theme-aware colors
- Test contrast ratios for accessibility

## Responsive Breakpoints
- xs: 300px
- sm: 600px
- md: 768px
- lg: 1024px
- xl: 1280px
- xxl: 1600px
- xxxl: 2400px

